---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Human Oversight as Default, Not Exception"
  description="Design workflows assuming humans will review and guide—make review the expected path, not an optional extra or exception."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Oversight as default" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Review Before Proceeding</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI has completed step 1. [Review before continuing] [Skip review] (not recommended)</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Review is the primary action; skipping is secondary and marked as not recommended.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Pause for Human Input</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI is waiting for your input on these items before proceeding: [3 items need review]
            [Continue when ready]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >The workflow pauses naturally for human review; it doesn't proceed automatically.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Auto-Proceed by Default (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI completes all steps automatically; review is hidden behind "Advanced options" or
            only available if users explicitly enable it. Most users never see review opportunities.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Human oversight becomes the exception; users miss opportunities to catch errors or
            guide the AI.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Make review the primary, expected path—pause workflows for human input rather than
      auto-proceeding.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Auto-proceed through all steps with review as an optional or hidden feature.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Design workflows that naturally pause at decision points where human judgment adds value.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Treat human oversight as an exception or advanced feature that most users won't need.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
